---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BrendaIntro from '../components/BrendaIntro.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  topic="About Brenda"
  description="Brenda is London Ontario's formally trained balloon artist, with an active mentor in Toronto. Custom installations for weddings, showers, corporate, birthdays, and graduations."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'About', url: '/about' },
  ]}
>
  <section class="about-hero section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">The artist</p>
      <h1>Brenda built this as a craft.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Most balloon vendors in London Ontario are self-taught. Brenda went to school for balloon artistry and stayed in active mentorship with one of Toronto's top balloon artists. Every install on Balloonia Events comes from that training.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <BrendaIntro variant="about" />

  <section class="about-body section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2>How Brenda works</h2>
      <p>
        Every booking starts with a written quote. Color palette, venue dimensions, materials, delivery time. Brenda reviews the details before she ever picks up a balloon, so the install matches what the customer planned.
      </p>
      <p>
        On the day, she arrives 2 to 3 hours before the event start, builds on-site, and leaves before guests show up. For ceiling installs and larger weddings, that runs 3 to 4 hours. Cleanup after the event can be added at booking.
      </p>

      <h2>The Toronto mentorship</h2>
      <p>
        The mentor relationship is live, not a course Brenda finished and shelved. It means she has direct access to technique escalation when a customer wants a structural geometric arch, an unusual ceiling install, or a custom themed build that most local vendors turn down. London hasn't seen that range of capability before.
      </p>

      <h2>The team behind the art</h2>
      <p>
        Brenda is the sole artist. Blake handles operations, scheduling, and customer communication during phone hours (Mon-Fri 9-6, Sat 11-6). It's a small operation. We don't pretend otherwise.
      </p>

      <div class="about-cta">
        <CTAButton href="/quote" variant="primary" size="lg">Work with Brenda</CTAButton>
        <CTAButton href="/portfolio" variant="secondary" size="lg">See the work</CTAButton>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-top: var(--space-7);
  }
</style>
